SIMPLE: nappy
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nappy
<hw>Nap"py</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From 1st
<er>Nap</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Inclined to sleep; sleepy; <as>as,
to feel <ex>nappy</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Tending to cause sleepiness; serving to make sleepy;
strong; heady; <as>as, <ex>nappy</ex> ale</as>.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Wyatt.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nappy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Nappy
<hw>Nap"py</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From 3d <er>Nap</er>.]</ety>
<def>Having a nap or pile; downy; shaggy.</def>
<rj><au>Holland.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nappy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Nappy
<hw>Nap"py</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Nappies</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[OE. <ets>nap</ets>, AS. <ets>hnaep</ets> cup,
bowl. See <er>Hanaper</er>.]</ety> <def>A round earthen dish, with a
flat bottom and sloping sides.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>nappie</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>nappy</ent>⟦br⟧

